{"id": "1426224144625832119", "channel_id": "1326453763355185215", "author_id": "88644018673582080", "author_name": "arkaether", "content": "I'd imagine that DISM recovered the silver but it's possible they weren't given pre-knowledge of Jenkin/weren't searching specifically for it, so they just recovered an unknown silver core and handed it over to Mythag for processing (it's been given a classification number and the wording there is pretty technical - I don't actually know who DISM is associated with and I can't find any other mentions of them. Are they a Mythia-aligned group? independent? Mythag-aligned?)\n\nYou do find Brown with the core when he's tired and sleeping at the end of his journey which could imply Brown ran off with it at some point to bring it to Jenkin's grave where you find him", "timestamp": "2025-10-10T15:05:34.042000+00:00"}
{"id": "1426224235969511424", "channel_id": "1326453763355185215", "author_id": "88644018673582080", "author_name": "arkaether", "content": "(realistically it's likely to just be a narrative oversight but I do think there's enough flexibility here in what we're given to make it possible to be consistent)", "timestamp": "2025-10-10T15:05:55.820000+00:00"}
{"id": "1426224515150516335", "channel_id": "1326453763355185215", "author_id": "289320818901778434", "author_name": "nikolazuli", "content": "yeah i believe so too", "timestamp": "2025-10-10T15:07:02.382000+00:00", "type": 19, "mentions": ["88644018673582080"], "reply_to": "1426224235969511424"}
{"id": "1426224742586781746", "channel_id": "1326453763355185215", "author_id": "88644018673582080", "author_name": "arkaether", "content": "ok interesting actually, checking that story in context\n\nSO\n\nstart of epilogue - alistair mentions keeper has been going to the wax museum with the Mystia Committee specifically to search for Jenkin's core, but nothing has been found\nHOWEVER keeper then floats the idea that perhaps someone deliberately took it", "timestamp": "2025-10-10T15:07:56.607000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": "2025-10-10T15:08:24.654000+00:00"}
{"id": "1426224868592193677", "channel_id": "1326453763355185215", "author_id": "289320818901778434", "author_name": "nikolazuli", "content": "as to DISM, i think the most likely answer is a Mystia task force, since they're the only known organization that's both knowledgeable about Dissolution and on friendly terms with Mythag that we known of", "timestamp": "2025-10-10T15:08:26.649000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": "2025-10-10T15:08:51.097000+00:00"}
{"id": "1426225010959188170", "channel_id": "1326453763355185215", "author_id": "88644018673582080", "author_name": "arkaether", "content": "if DISM is either a third party or non-Mythag-aligned group, they probably found the core before Keeper, didn't know it was Jenkin's/wasn't in the loop and just processed it as a standard core for Mythag handover", "timestamp": "2025-10-10T15:09:00.592000+00:00"}
{"id": "1426225254967021648", "channel_id": "1326453763355185215", "author_id": "88644018673582080", "author_name": "arkaether", "content": "Keeper has no pull or influence with Mystia afaik so even if Keeper was deliberately tagging along with Mystia to search for the core as part of the post-operation area neutralization, I doubt they would have gone out of their way to prioritize your goals", "timestamp": "2025-10-10T15:09:58.768000+00:00"}
{"id": "1426225534764847248", "channel_id": "1326453763355185215", "author_id": "88644018673582080", "author_name": "arkaether", "content": "so it's basically keeper searches for jenkin core for a month > finds nothing > turns out it was because DISM already searched and found it and handed it over to Mythag > at some point before Mythag processes/investigates the core properly and realizes it's Jenkin and informs the Keeper, Brown's Great Adventure™ begins and he yoinks the core and brings it to Jenkin's grave where you find it", "timestamp": "2025-10-10T15:11:05.477000+00:00"}
{"id": "1426225755750404177", "channel_id": "1326453763355185215", "author_id": "289320818901778434", "author_name": "nikolazuli", "content": "we know that Mystia operates as first responders to D-phenomena, and that within Londinium, they're willing to let Mythag investigators take the lead in co-op operations since they know mythag is more suited for t task", "timestamp": "2025-10-10T15:11:58.164000+00:00"}
